paragraphs.text: you've been lying in bed for a week now wondering how long it'll take you haven't spoken or looked at her in all that time it's the easiest line you could break she's been going 'round her business as usual always with that melancholy smile but you were too busy looking into your affairs to see those tiny tears in her eyes
tiny tears make up an ocean tiny tears make up a sea let them pour out pour out all over don't let them pour all over me

how can you hurt someone so much you're supposed to care for someone you said you'd always be there for but when that water breaks you know you're gonna cry, cry when those tears start rolling you'll be back
